messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

+raymond as this may have impact on our tests.

Patch Set 1:

There is a minor changed that needs to be done in gradle-experimental/build.gradle.

I am not sure I understand how does changing this file to gradle-2.4-all.zip affects editing gradle files.
Uploaded patch set 2: Commit message was updated.

Patch Set 2:

> There is a minor changed that needs to be done in gradle-experimental/build.gradle.
 > 
 > I am not sure I understand how does changing this file to
 > gradle-2.4-all.zip affects editing gradle files.

Fixed the breaking change here:
https://android-review.googlesource.com/#/c/151412/

Most groups use these gradle distributions when building unbundled apps at Google. During development Android Studio will present a help link suggesting to install the -all.zip distribution to provide code completion / javadoc and source code while editing gradle files. If you select the option when using an unbundled app it will install -all.zip locally, but break the unbundled app build so this was the discussed solution. Happy to point you at some internal threads on the topic if that would be useful.
